channel.name: tavares-teacup
channel.topic:
Hey Everyone! If you're reading this that means you're being awesome. Here in Tavare's Teacup (name subject to change) there are a few rules to help keep everything running smoothly and awesomely. Here's a quick overview on when you should/should not do anything in regards to the bot.

**Minor grammatical mistake or non-urgent bug:**
Report it in the form, these aren't super urgent so there isn't a necessity to contact anyone directly!

**"Minor incident"** 
These are things you should ping Ghost about. These include errors from the bot, or bugs such as using the cakeday command and it not functioning as expected.

**"Major incident"**
These are incidents that need attention as soon as possible, so ping the Botmaster Role! This includes commands related to the question queue not functioning properly.

**"Critical Incident"**
These are red alert incidents, if the bot server is compromised, the bot starts spamming or sending out scam links, ping the Whisper and Researcher roles ***IMMEDIATELY.*** They will kick the bot and then contact the bot masters to rectify the situation.

In all these cases. pings are the required form of contact. Bot masters or staff members may need to bring other members into the conversation and it is easier if it's where everything can easily be seen, so please don't DM the botmasters!
